1
00:00:19,757 --> 00:00:23,561
2026 MAY

2
00:00:46,618 --> 00:00:47,785
TAXI

3
00:01:37,368 --> 00:01:38,403
Welcome back.

4
00:01:39,070 --> 00:01:40,104
I'm home.

5
00:01:41,339 --> 00:01:44,175
Today, I made your favorite
hamburger steak.

6
00:01:47,512 --> 00:01:48,880
Thank you, as always.

7
00:01:48,947 --> 00:01:50,081
It's nothing, really.

8
00:01:50,148 --> 00:01:55,253
I have to say, my cooking skills lately
have been improving rapidly.

9
00:01:56,854 --> 00:01:59,157
By any chance,
did you get fired from school again?

10
00:02:00,658 --> 00:02:01,659
What?

11
00:02:04,295 --> 00:02:06,798
You're making hamburger steak
just to butter me up.

12
00:02:06,864 --> 00:02:08,566
Get your act together already!

13
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:11,502
Even now, you ride around
on that huge motorcycle,

14
00:02:11,569 --> 00:02:14,372
acting cool in front of students,
saying "It's great,"

15
00:02:14,439 --> 00:02:16,841
yet every single school
you go to, you get fired.

16
00:02:16,908 --> 00:02:18,843
You're already 52.

17
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:21,779
Normally, this is the age people
become vice principals!

18
00:02:22,914 --> 00:02:26,150
Or is it that, since I still bring
money home, you aren't worried?

19
00:02:26,217 --> 00:02:28,786
No, sorry, I don't think like that.

20
00:02:28,853 --> 00:02:32,991
It looks like I'm just getting
mad at you, but that's not it.

21
00:02:33,057 --> 00:02:36,527
It's because no matter how many times
I say it, you just don't listen!

22
00:02:37,095 --> 00:02:41,332
The last time you got fired,
you said, "I didn't do anything wrong."

23
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:43,735
Then let me ask you,

24
00:02:44,302 --> 00:02:48,106
what on earth even is this
"Great Teacher" thing you talk about?

25
00:02:48,172 --> 00:02:49,440
What kind of teacher is it?

26
00:02:50,241 --> 00:02:53,278
Well, that's, you know…

27
00:02:53,344 --> 00:02:55,880
Someone who cares about the students…

28
00:02:55,947 --> 00:02:57,348
I can't hear you.

29
00:02:57,415 --> 00:03:00,785
What it means is, as a teacher, I…

30
00:03:02,587 --> 00:03:03,521
Oh, enough already.

31
00:03:04,656 --> 00:03:08,693
Just find a new job
as quickly as possible.

32
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:11,129
Promise me that you won't
quit that school.

33
00:03:11,829 --> 00:03:15,667
And come up with a proper answer
for what a "Great Teacher" is.

34
00:03:16,234 --> 00:03:17,468
If you can't do that…

35
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:19,804
What?

36
00:03:23,408 --> 00:03:24,242
DIVORCE FORM

37
00:03:24,309 --> 00:03:26,210
Hey! You're joking, right?

38
00:03:26,277 --> 00:03:27,211
I am serious.

39
00:03:27,812 --> 00:03:30,281
I'll be going back to my parents' house.

40
00:03:30,348 --> 00:03:31,282
What?

41
00:03:31,783 --> 00:03:34,786
By the way,
your hamburger steak is burning!

42
00:03:35,453 --> 00:03:36,988
Oh, crap!

43
00:03:37,722 --> 00:03:38,656
Wait!

44
00:03:39,324 --> 00:03:41,092
It's hot!

45
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:43,428
Azusa! Hold on…

46
00:03:43,494 --> 00:03:45,830
Oh, no! I have to turn the fire down.

47
00:03:46,764 --> 00:03:48,199
It's hot!

48
00:05:13,284 --> 00:05:15,186
CV - EIKICHI ONIZUKA

49
00:05:17,054 --> 00:05:19,957
It seems you have resigned
from quite a number of schools.

50
00:05:20,024 --> 00:05:21,426
That was because…

51
00:05:21,492 --> 00:05:25,897
my educational philosophy
did not align with the schools.

52
00:05:25,963 --> 00:05:27,031
<i>Rumors say the reason is</i>

53
00:05:27,098 --> 00:05:29,600
that you once occupied a school,
were violent to colleagues,

54
00:05:29,667 --> 00:05:33,604
verbally abusive toward parents,
and even sexually harassed students?

55
00:05:33,671 --> 00:05:38,409
No, I did all of that
for the students' sake.

56
00:05:38,476 --> 00:05:40,278
Even if that was the case,

57
00:05:40,344 --> 00:05:44,715
I don't think any school would hire
someone over 50 with such a background.

58
00:05:45,283 --> 00:05:48,619
No matter how severe
the teacher shortage is right now.

59
00:05:51,022 --> 00:05:53,558
All right, please open your mouth.

60
00:06:03,868 --> 00:06:05,303
Mr. Onizuka.

61
00:06:05,369 --> 00:06:09,440
The only option left for this tooth
is to extract it and get an implant.

62
00:06:10,007 --> 00:06:11,909
ISABE DENTAL

63
00:06:11,976 --> 00:06:14,745
One, ten, one hundred, one thousand,
ten thousand, one hundred thousand…

64
00:06:14,812 --> 00:06:15,746
What?

65
00:06:16,314 --> 00:06:18,616
Are implants really that expensive?

66
00:06:18,683 --> 00:06:21,352
299,800 yen… I…

67
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,321
Woah! Stop!

68
00:06:24,455 --> 00:06:27,191
OSARU DELIVERY

69
00:06:27,258 --> 00:06:28,626
It hurts!

70
00:06:28,693 --> 00:06:30,061
Do you want to die, idiot?

71
00:06:30,127 --> 00:06:31,996
Shut up, bastard!

72
00:06:38,936 --> 00:06:40,071
Is that you, Onicchi?

73
00:06:40,137 --> 00:06:41,806
Oh, it's you, Masaru!

74
00:06:42,373 --> 00:06:44,709
Why were you spacing out like that?
That's dangerous.

75
00:06:44,775 --> 00:06:46,277
-I have a lot going on.
-A lot?

76
00:06:49,747 --> 00:06:51,716
Come on, don't look so pathetic.

77
00:06:51,782 --> 00:06:54,051
It's not like Ms. Fuyutsuki
will divorce you, right?

78
00:06:54,118 --> 00:06:55,319
What?

79
00:06:56,087 --> 00:06:57,321
Wait, seriously?

80
00:06:57,388 --> 00:06:58,389
Uh…

81
00:06:59,123 --> 00:07:01,792
I need to find a job
or I'm in deep trouble.

82
00:07:01,859 --> 00:07:03,561
No one will hire me.

83
00:07:04,962 --> 00:07:07,098
We've been married for 25 years,

84
00:07:07,164 --> 00:07:10,768
and I thought we'd be together
until our hair turned white,

85
00:07:10,835 --> 00:07:13,304
but at this rate, it's truly over.

86
00:07:14,672 --> 00:07:16,340
Oh, I know.

87
00:07:16,407 --> 00:07:18,809
Why don't you try
for my daughter's high school?

88
00:07:18,876 --> 00:07:20,945
Wait, you have a daughter in high school?

89
00:07:21,012 --> 00:07:22,847
Didn't I tell you last time we met?

90
00:07:22,914 --> 00:07:24,382
I'm already 43, you know.

91
00:07:24,448 --> 00:07:28,486
To earn money for my daughter's tuition,
I started working as a delivery driver.

92
00:07:29,253 --> 00:07:33,658
A hopeless delinquent like you
is now the father of a high school girl.

93
00:07:33,724 --> 00:07:37,361
Quit getting all sentimental over
your former student's happy life, and go.

94
00:07:37,428 --> 00:07:39,130
I'll email you the details.

95
00:07:39,196 --> 00:07:42,867
Oh, right, that school
is run by a large corporation,

96
00:07:42,934 --> 00:07:45,369
and they are looking
for a teacher right now.

97
00:07:45,436 --> 00:07:48,239
Got it? They are a big corporation.

98
00:07:48,306 --> 00:07:50,775
Wear a suit and tie when you go. Got it?

99
00:07:50,841 --> 00:07:51,676
Yes.

100
00:08:00,718 --> 00:08:02,753
Let's do this.

101
00:08:06,057 --> 00:08:07,024
Excuse me…

102
00:08:07,091 --> 00:08:10,761
I would like to meet with the person
in charge of teacher recruitment

103
00:08:10,828 --> 00:08:12,263
for the school your company runs…

104
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:14,031
We've been waiting for you.

105
00:08:14,098 --> 00:08:15,633
I will guide you.

106
00:08:19,437 --> 00:08:23,274
<i>What a magnificent building.</i>

107
00:08:23,341 --> 00:08:27,011
Students who attend a school
run by a fine company like yours

108
00:08:27,078 --> 00:08:28,980
must be truly happy.

109
00:08:34,251 --> 00:08:35,720
Mr. Onizuka.

110
00:08:35,786 --> 00:08:36,654
Yes?

111
00:08:37,588 --> 00:08:38,422
You've passed.

112
00:08:38,990 --> 00:08:39,757
What?

113
00:08:39,824 --> 00:08:41,859
Would you come to our high school?

114
00:08:41,926 --> 00:08:44,061
No way? Are you sure?

115
00:08:44,795 --> 00:08:46,797
Come on, don't you remember me?

116
00:08:47,732 --> 00:08:48,566
What?

117
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:52,136
Back in Kairei High School,
Class 2-C, I was in your class.

118
00:08:53,638 --> 00:08:56,240
Oh! Yes!

119
00:08:56,307 --> 00:08:59,076
Um, I remember. You're…

120
00:09:01,312 --> 00:09:03,247
You tried to cheat just now.

121
00:09:03,314 --> 00:09:05,716
No, I would never do that!

122
00:09:05,783 --> 00:09:07,852
I totally remember you.

123
00:09:07,918 --> 00:09:12,089
But could you just tell me the first part?

124
00:09:12,156 --> 00:09:13,324
Today, you see…

125
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:16,227
My tooth hurts, and I'm not feeling well.

126
00:09:17,828 --> 00:09:19,063
It's "Mi."

127
00:09:19,964 --> 00:09:21,599
By the way, what's next?

128
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,501
"Ya."

129
00:09:25,036 --> 00:09:26,003
A bit more.

130
00:09:26,671 --> 00:09:27,505
"Za."

131
00:09:29,206 --> 00:09:31,308
Could it be, the next part is…

132
00:09:32,076 --> 00:09:32,743
"Wa?"

133
00:09:33,377 --> 00:09:35,246
It's Miyazawa.

134
00:09:35,312 --> 00:09:37,682
Ryunosuke Miyazawa. Ryunosuke!

135
00:09:37,748 --> 00:09:38,816
Yes.

136
00:09:38,883 --> 00:09:40,117
What the heck?

137
00:09:40,184 --> 00:09:41,919
You're a big shot now,
I didn't recognize you.

138
00:09:41,986 --> 00:09:43,988
Besides, you see…

139
00:09:44,689 --> 00:09:48,059
I only remember first names anyway.

140
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:49,060
That's right.

141
00:09:49,126 --> 00:09:52,063
What the heck, you're working
at such a great company.

142
00:09:52,129 --> 00:09:53,597
You're amazing, Ryunosuke.

143
00:09:54,331 --> 00:09:56,467
Quite the opposite, you saved me.

144
00:09:56,534 --> 00:09:58,936
It's only May, yet a teacher just quit,

145
00:09:59,003 --> 00:10:01,939
so the higher-ups told me
to fill the vacancy. I was panicking.

146
00:10:03,374 --> 00:10:06,444
And I was looking for a passionate teacher

147
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:09,180
who could ignite a passion
in the current students.

148
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,817
So, meeting you must be fate…

149
00:10:14,585 --> 00:10:15,553
Well…

150
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:20,891
Will you really come to our high school?

151
00:10:23,961 --> 00:10:26,197
I'm not sure…

152
00:10:26,263 --> 00:10:30,201
I've actually received pretty good offers
from other schools too, you know.

153
00:10:47,318 --> 00:10:48,252
All right.

154
00:10:53,891 --> 00:10:55,326
Let's do this!

155
00:10:57,328 --> 00:10:58,829
Good morning.

156
00:11:00,064 --> 00:11:03,834
Our school's slogan is
"Nurturing Future Leaders."

157
00:11:03,901 --> 00:11:06,470
We have classes using
state-of-the-art technology,

158
00:11:06,537 --> 00:11:10,274
and classes on investing
for when they get a job in the future.

159
00:11:10,341 --> 00:11:12,576
-I also teach those classes.
-Good morning.

160
00:11:13,144 --> 00:11:16,046
We also accept students
who were truant or have issues

161
00:11:16,113 --> 00:11:18,482
as part of our efforts
to contribute to society.

162
00:11:18,549 --> 00:11:19,650
Good morning.

163
00:11:21,819 --> 00:11:24,655
Hey, what is everyone holding?

164
00:11:25,523 --> 00:11:27,858
Those are tablets provided by the school.

165
00:11:27,925 --> 00:11:30,594
Various data and information is entered,

166
00:11:30,661 --> 00:11:33,664
and students and teachers
can easily interact via chat.

167
00:11:33,731 --> 00:11:37,201
It helps create an environment
for a comfortable school life.

168
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:44,642
Somehow this place…

169
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:45,709
Yes?

170
00:11:47,611 --> 00:11:49,346
It feels more like a company

171
00:11:50,548 --> 00:11:52,249
than a school.

172
00:11:54,552 --> 00:11:56,854
PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE

173
00:11:56,921 --> 00:11:59,857
This is Principal Ohkubo.

174
00:11:59,924 --> 00:12:01,792
PRINCIPAL

175
00:12:01,859 --> 00:12:03,727
I'm Eikichi Onizuka.

176
00:12:03,794 --> 00:12:06,463
I will dedicate my life to working here!

177
00:12:07,264 --> 00:12:08,599
Well, thank you.

178
00:12:08,666 --> 00:12:09,934
Over there is the Vice Principal…

179
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,769
Hello, nice to meet you. I will be…

180
00:12:16,006 --> 00:12:17,274
Onizuka?

181
00:12:17,842 --> 00:12:19,109
Why are you here?

182
00:12:19,176 --> 00:12:21,078
Oh, long time, no see!

183
00:12:21,712 --> 00:12:22,880
What was it again?

184
00:12:23,681 --> 00:12:26,483
You were there, weren't you?
Back at Seirin Academy,

185
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:29,286
you were one of the two people
who gave me a hard time.

186
00:12:29,353 --> 00:12:30,287
I remember now.

187
00:12:30,354 --> 00:12:31,589
Uchiyamada!

188
00:12:32,223 --> 00:12:33,357
It's Nakamaru.

189
00:12:33,424 --> 00:12:35,025
Oh, that one.

190
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:38,662
Principal, let's pass on this guy.

191
00:12:38,729 --> 00:12:41,599
He's bound to cause catastrophic trouble.

192
00:12:41,665 --> 00:12:45,002
Even if you say so, I don't have
authority over personnel matters.

193
00:12:45,069 --> 00:12:48,239
Mr. Miyazawa, why did you hire
someone like this?

194
00:12:48,806 --> 00:12:52,309
I was his student, and when all's said
and done, he's a really good teacher.

195
00:12:52,376 --> 00:12:56,347
Even so,
look at this terrible work history.

196
00:12:56,413 --> 00:12:58,816
This man is a former biker gang member.

197
00:12:58,883 --> 00:12:59,717
What?

198
00:12:59,783 --> 00:13:01,619
Is that so?

199
00:13:01,685 --> 00:13:03,587
Come on, Mr. Nakamaru.

200
00:13:03,654 --> 00:13:06,857
I'm 52 now, so I won't
do reckless things like I used to.

201
00:13:06,924 --> 00:13:09,026
How can anything you say be trusted?

202
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:13,030
After 30 years of hardships, in the year
I finally became Vice Principal,

203
00:13:13,097 --> 00:13:15,933
why does an unqualified teacher
like you have to come along?

204
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,034
To my school!

205
00:13:19,003 --> 00:13:20,604
What's with that look?

206
00:13:20,671 --> 00:13:22,606
No, if I recall…

207
00:13:22,673 --> 00:13:26,143
Back then, you stepped aside to let
another teacher become Vice Principal,

208
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:28,512
so I thought you had become
a better teacher.

209
00:13:28,579 --> 00:13:31,315
But you've reverted to an unpleasant guy.

210
00:13:31,382 --> 00:13:33,417
-What did you say?
-Oh, I'm sorry.

211
00:13:33,484 --> 00:13:37,922
If I get fired this time, it will be truly
disastrous, so I'll take it seriously.

212
00:13:37,988 --> 00:13:41,258
I'm happy to be able to teach
at such a wonderful school.

213
00:13:41,325 --> 00:13:44,328
The future of Japan is right here! Yes!

214
00:13:52,603 --> 00:13:54,038
STAFF ROOM

215
00:13:54,104 --> 00:13:55,739
Good morning.

216
00:13:56,774 --> 00:13:57,841
-Morning.
-Good morning.

217
00:13:57,908 --> 00:14:01,011
Ms. Kashiwabara, you're cutting it
pretty close today too.

218
00:14:01,078 --> 00:14:03,213
I'm sorry, my horoscope wasn't good today

219
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:07,017
so I thought about not coming. Then I
thought that wouldn't be right either.

220
00:14:07,084 --> 00:14:08,986
And besides, I'm not late.

221
00:14:09,053 --> 00:14:10,854
Going at your own pace as always.

222
00:14:10,921 --> 00:14:14,858
Your generation really dislikes
wasting effort, right?

223
00:14:15,426 --> 00:14:18,095
In our time, such a thing was unthinkable.

224
00:14:18,662 --> 00:14:21,699
And your clothing is also
a bit much for a teacher…

225
00:14:21,765 --> 00:14:22,933
Mr. Murayama.

226
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,502
What you're saying
is harassment, you know.

227
00:14:25,569 --> 00:14:28,038
I'm sorry, I didn't mean it that way…

228
00:14:28,105 --> 00:14:29,239
It's fine, isn't it?

229
00:14:29,306 --> 00:14:31,842
Ms. Kashiwabara does her job properly,

230
00:14:31,909 --> 00:14:34,211
and I've never heard complaints
from students, right?

231
00:14:34,278 --> 00:14:36,747
I'm still lacking
compared to you, Ms. Koizumi.

232
00:14:40,784 --> 00:14:41,986
Hold on!

233
00:14:42,052 --> 00:14:43,087
Everyone.

234
00:14:43,654 --> 00:14:44,922
Allow me to introduce him.

235
00:14:45,823 --> 00:14:49,293
He will be taking over Class 1-B,
from its previous teacher,

236
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:51,462
teaching Japanese History…

237
00:14:51,528 --> 00:14:53,263
I'm Eikichi Onizuka!

238
00:14:55,032 --> 00:14:56,300
If anyone among you

239
00:14:56,367 --> 00:14:59,136
knows the answer to
what a "Great Teacher" is…

240
00:14:59,203 --> 00:15:00,037
Ms. Kashiwabara,

241
00:15:00,104 --> 00:15:03,807
please mentor him, since you're
the assistant teacher of Class 1-B.

242
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:05,209
Sure.

243
00:15:05,275 --> 00:15:07,611
Mr. Nakamaru,
I'm not done with my greeting yet.

244
00:15:08,245 --> 00:15:11,648
-If nothing changes, my wife will--
-Everyone, have a good day.

245
00:15:19,656 --> 00:15:20,858
You can have this.

246
00:15:20,924 --> 00:15:21,759
What?

247
00:15:21,825 --> 00:15:25,729
I've put together necessary info, like
what lessons were already done in April.

248
00:15:25,796 --> 00:15:26,730
Right.

249
00:15:26,797 --> 00:15:28,465
Thank you, this helps a lot.

250
00:15:28,532 --> 00:15:31,802
It's nothing, it was easier
to write it down than to explain it.

251
00:15:32,469 --> 00:15:35,773
By the way, why did
the previous teacher quit?

252
00:15:35,839 --> 00:15:38,075
It seems he was struggling
with his mental health.

253
00:15:38,642 --> 00:15:39,476
What?

254
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:42,780
Does that mean
there was some problem with the class?

255
00:15:43,347 --> 00:15:44,748
No, nothing like that.

256
00:15:44,815 --> 00:15:45,883
Right.

257
00:15:45,949 --> 00:15:48,919
Is there anything
I should be careful about?

258
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:53,424
Maybe it's my age, but I don't really get
high school students these days.

259
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:56,860
Just do as you like.
You're the homeroom teacher, after all.

260
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:01,565
All right.

261
00:16:05,135 --> 00:16:06,670
CLASS 1-B

262
00:16:09,606 --> 00:16:11,842
-Good morning.
-Let's go!

263
00:16:12,576 --> 00:16:14,311
Good morning.

264
00:16:14,378 --> 00:16:16,613
Before we start homeroom,
let me introduce him.

265
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:19,183
-Starting today, he will be your home--
-Excuse me.

266
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:21,885
I'll take it from here.

267
00:16:21,952 --> 00:16:23,220
Right, please go ahead.

268
00:16:32,162 --> 00:16:34,898
EIKICHI ONIZUKA

269
00:16:36,066 --> 00:16:40,270
I'm Eikichi Onizuka,
your homeroom teacher starting today.

270
00:16:42,506 --> 00:16:43,507
Nice to meet you.

271
00:16:45,576 --> 00:16:47,644
Let's see…

272
00:16:47,711 --> 00:16:50,247
I have been teaching for 27 years.

273
00:16:50,314 --> 00:16:51,815
My motto is…

274
00:16:51,882 --> 00:16:56,053
Oh, we've already looked you up,
so we're good.

275
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:59,056
-What?
-You seem to be quite a unique teacher.

276
00:16:59,123 --> 00:16:59,957
Interesting.

277
00:17:00,023 --> 00:17:01,225
-Woah.
-He's funny!

278
00:17:02,092 --> 00:17:03,093
Then…

279
00:17:03,894 --> 00:17:05,229
I'm taking attendance.

280
00:17:06,630 --> 00:17:07,865
Ayano Ashida.

281
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:10,667
What?

282
00:17:10,734 --> 00:17:12,336
Is Ashida absent?

283
00:17:14,738 --> 00:17:15,606
What?

284
00:17:15,672 --> 00:17:18,175
Oh, if you're here, speak up!

285
00:17:19,009 --> 00:17:20,244
I'm sorry.

286
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:23,480
The rule here is to address
both boys and girls with honorifics,

287
00:17:23,547 --> 00:17:24,648
so I was a bit startled.

288
00:17:27,584 --> 00:17:28,552
Is that so?

289
00:17:29,119 --> 00:17:30,854
It was in the memo I gave you.

290
00:17:30,921 --> 00:17:31,755
Oh, right.

291
00:17:32,556 --> 00:17:33,390
But…

292
00:17:34,091 --> 00:17:36,293
Isn't that a bit too distant?

293
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:39,062
Let's give you a nickname, come on.
Since it's Ashida…

294
00:17:39,630 --> 00:17:40,597
Something like Asshi.

295
00:17:40,664 --> 00:17:43,367
Why is there a need to do such a thing?

296
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:47,905
That way we can get closer faster,
you guys can call me Onicchi too.

297
00:17:47,971 --> 00:17:48,872
I'm sorry.

298
00:17:48,939 --> 00:17:50,073
I don't really get it.

299
00:17:50,774 --> 00:17:53,177
High school life
will be more fun that way.

300
00:17:53,243 --> 00:17:56,213
I don't think school is meant to be
enjoyed, it's a step toward the future.

301
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,814
Hold on, kid.

302
00:17:57,881 --> 00:18:00,651
You have to enjoy your youth!

303
00:18:00,717 --> 00:18:01,618
What is "youth"?

304
00:18:03,253 --> 00:18:06,657
Running toward the sunset,
getting excited at mixer parties,

305
00:18:07,224 --> 00:18:09,092
eating mystery hotpots,
doing tests of courage.

306
00:18:09,159 --> 00:18:12,095
Mixer parties, mystery hotpots,
tests of courage…

307
00:18:12,162 --> 00:18:15,065
I don't know what they mean,
so I'll look them up.

308
00:18:19,203 --> 00:18:20,237
Hey…

309
00:18:20,804 --> 00:18:23,006
Hey, are you kidding me?

310
00:18:26,843 --> 00:18:27,678
What?

311
00:18:28,478 --> 00:18:30,113
Is that guy absent?

312
00:18:31,481 --> 00:18:34,384
He hasn't come for a while.

313
00:18:35,085 --> 00:18:37,020
How long is "a while"?

314
00:18:37,087 --> 00:18:38,288
Who knows?

315
00:18:39,223 --> 00:18:42,426
What's their name? Someone tell me.

316
00:18:42,492 --> 00:18:44,895
What was that guy's name again?

317
00:18:46,296 --> 00:18:47,664
Don't ask me.

318
00:18:48,332 --> 00:18:49,866
It's Kenta Katayama.

319
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:52,836
Ah, there was a guy like that.

320
00:18:52,903 --> 00:18:54,004
What was he like?

321
00:18:56,006 --> 00:18:57,574
I can't even remember his face.

322
00:18:58,275 --> 00:18:59,710
It's kind of a mystery.

323
00:19:00,510 --> 00:19:01,712
You…

324
00:19:02,246 --> 00:19:03,547
Aren't you worried?

325
00:19:03,614 --> 00:19:05,148
What are we supposed to do?

326
00:19:05,215 --> 00:19:07,417
Isn't that your job, Mr. Onizuka?

327
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:16,159
STAFF ROOM

328
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:24,268
Kenta Katayama did come
for about two weeks after April,

329
00:19:24,334 --> 00:19:26,136
but he has been absent ever since.

330
00:19:26,803 --> 00:19:27,871
The reason?

331
00:19:27,938 --> 00:19:31,541
We don't really know, but at least
it doesn't seem to be bullying.

332
00:19:31,608 --> 00:19:35,045
By the way, that was also
in the memo I gave you earlier.

333
00:19:35,112 --> 00:19:35,979
What?

334
00:19:40,317 --> 00:19:41,351
I'm sorry.

335
00:19:42,185 --> 00:19:44,321
Lately, I can't read small print.

336
00:19:45,555 --> 00:19:49,092
Didn't anyone try to persuade Kenta
to come to school?

337
00:19:49,159 --> 00:19:52,162
The previous homeroom teacher
went to his house once,

338
00:19:52,229 --> 00:19:55,132
but it seems Kenta said
he "doesn't need to go to school."

339
00:19:55,932 --> 00:19:56,767
And then?

340
00:19:57,768 --> 00:19:58,969
That's all that happened.

341
00:20:04,107 --> 00:20:06,076
FOR FIREFIGHTING

342
00:20:06,143 --> 00:20:09,012
Kenta Katayama.

343
00:20:12,382 --> 00:20:13,517
Wait a minute.

344
00:20:14,251 --> 00:20:18,422
This device, can it also
be used to watch "that stuff"?

345
00:20:21,191 --> 00:20:24,261
PORN VIDEOS

346
00:20:24,828 --> 00:20:26,663
What are you doing?

347
00:20:29,599 --> 00:20:31,435
Mr. Onizuka.

348
00:20:31,501 --> 00:20:33,103
Nothing really.

349
00:20:36,506 --> 00:20:40,677
By the way, you can't view
adult sites on that tablet.

350
00:20:40,744 --> 00:20:43,814
You idiot, no way I'd do that.
How old do you think I am?

351
00:20:45,015 --> 00:20:46,583
Can I have one too?

352
00:20:50,987 --> 00:20:52,255
That's it.

353
00:20:56,693 --> 00:20:57,661
Thank you.

354
00:21:09,439 --> 00:21:13,176
You used to scold me a lot back then.
For smoking cigarettes on the rooftop.

355
00:21:13,744 --> 00:21:14,578
Right.

356
00:21:15,178 --> 00:21:17,614
How nostalgic. I did do that.

357
00:21:18,582 --> 00:21:20,584
How are the kids in the class?

358
00:21:21,218 --> 00:21:26,189
Well, they're detached,
always looking at their tablets.

359
00:21:26,256 --> 00:21:29,326
They don't look at me when I talk,
which is frustrating.

360
00:21:29,393 --> 00:21:32,362
I understand how you feel,
but please be careful.

361
00:21:33,029 --> 00:21:35,599
Our school has a teacher feedback system.

362
00:21:35,665 --> 00:21:37,334
Feed…

363
00:21:37,401 --> 00:21:38,602
What is that?

364
00:21:39,169 --> 00:21:41,538
Students anonymously evaluate teachers

365
00:21:41,605 --> 00:21:44,608
on a ten-point scale
from plus five to minus five.

366
00:21:44,674 --> 00:21:46,610
This is the current ranking…

367
00:21:46,676 --> 00:21:48,145
By the way, who is number one?

368
00:21:49,446 --> 00:21:51,181
It's Ms. Koizumi, the English teacher.

369
00:21:51,248 --> 00:21:52,616
KOIZUMI - 810 POINTS

370
00:21:52,682 --> 00:21:54,284
RANKING (WEEKLY)

371
00:21:57,354 --> 00:21:58,889
<i>She uses a projector</i>

372
00:21:59,523 --> 00:22:03,627
<i>to conduct classes in a game-like format,</i>
<i>so the students love her.</i>

373
00:22:05,729 --> 00:22:07,798
Give explanations for interior
and exterior angles…

374
00:22:08,498 --> 00:22:12,068
<i>Also, Mr. Abe, the math teacher,</i>
<i>is quite popular too.</i>

375
00:22:12,669 --> 00:22:15,539
<i>He cuts out waste and prides himself</i>

376
00:22:15,605 --> 00:22:18,074
<i>on cutting-edge classes</i>
<i>using generative AI.</i>

377
00:22:18,642 --> 00:22:21,411
The length of EF can be found to be two.

378
00:22:22,045 --> 00:22:24,681
<i>Are there any unpopular teachers?</i>

379
00:22:24,748 --> 00:22:29,252
In the year 1789, August 26…

380
00:22:29,319 --> 00:22:31,455
<i>I shouldn't say this out loud,</i>

381
00:22:31,521 --> 00:22:33,890
<i>but maybe Mr. Murayama,</i>
<i>the world history teacher?</i>

382
00:22:34,458 --> 00:22:37,627
<i>He just reads from the textbook,</i>
<i>and never scolds students,</i>

383
00:22:37,694 --> 00:22:40,063
<i>so everyone does other stuff in his class.</i>

384
00:22:42,365 --> 00:22:46,269
Mr. Onizuka,
if low evaluations continue for too long,

385
00:22:47,070 --> 00:22:49,906
you'll be removed
as homeroom teacher, face a pay cut,

386
00:22:50,507 --> 00:22:53,910
and eventually be dismissed,
so please be careful.

387
00:22:53,977 --> 00:22:57,080
Well, I do want to avoid that.

388
00:22:57,981 --> 00:23:00,750
But if you reach
number one, you get a bonus.

389
00:23:02,352 --> 00:23:04,521
What? Really?

390
00:23:05,722 --> 00:23:06,790
Mr. Onizuka.

391
00:23:06,857 --> 00:23:09,059
You've always loved money, haven't you?

392
00:23:09,626 --> 00:23:11,061
No, you see…

393
00:23:11,127 --> 00:23:13,797
I've caused my wife trouble
for so long, so…

394
00:23:21,838 --> 00:23:22,672
Right.

395
00:23:23,540 --> 00:23:26,710
Does anyone have any questions?

396
00:23:26,776 --> 00:23:28,078
We’re good.

397
00:23:28,645 --> 00:23:31,748
Come on, don't be shy,
you can ask me anything.

398
00:23:31,815 --> 00:23:35,085
Why are you smiling so much?

399
00:23:35,652 --> 00:23:38,722
This is just how my face is…

400
00:23:40,924 --> 00:23:42,058
Oh.

401
00:23:43,126 --> 00:23:45,262
Great work today.

402
00:23:45,829 --> 00:23:49,332
If you ever have any problems,
don't hesitate to reach out to me.

403
00:23:49,933 --> 00:23:52,802
I'm Onizuka.
Eikichi Onizuka, nice to meet you.

404
00:23:53,436 --> 00:23:55,805
You can call me Onicchi.

405
00:24:01,077 --> 00:24:02,412
Mr. Onizuka.

406
00:24:02,479 --> 00:24:03,346
Yes?

407
00:24:04,614 --> 00:24:05,749
I'll be leaving now.

408
00:24:05,815 --> 00:24:07,918
What? Are you heading home already?

409
00:24:07,984 --> 00:24:10,420
Yes, I’ve done everything I needed to do.

410
00:24:16,159 --> 00:24:17,494
Bye then.

411
00:24:33,343 --> 00:24:36,613
That's a pretty nice house.

412
00:24:43,086 --> 00:24:44,087
<i>Yes?</i>

413
00:24:45,789 --> 00:24:48,058
Is Kenta Katayama here?

414
00:24:49,626 --> 00:24:50,760
<i>Who is it?</i>

415
00:24:51,995 --> 00:24:57,200
My name is Eikichi Onizuka,
Kenta's new homeroom teacher.

416
00:25:24,227 --> 00:25:26,363
Are you Kenta?

417
00:25:27,797 --> 00:25:28,732
You need something?

418
00:25:28,798 --> 00:25:31,568
Isn't it obvious?
Why aren't you coming to school?

419
00:25:31,635 --> 00:25:32,502
No point telling you.

420
00:25:33,236 --> 00:25:35,372
-Why?
-Because I'll die soon.

421
00:25:35,438 --> 00:25:37,674
No way! Are you sick?

422
00:25:37,741 --> 00:25:40,577
I'm not. There's just no point in living.

423
00:25:41,144 --> 00:25:42,846
What are you talking about?

424
00:25:42,912 --> 00:25:45,482
If you come to school,
there are lots of fun things.

425
00:25:45,548 --> 00:25:46,750
Like what?

426
00:25:46,816 --> 00:25:51,087
For example, making lots of friends.

427
00:25:52,522 --> 00:25:54,491
I went for a little bit in April,

428
00:25:54,991 --> 00:25:58,695
but everyone was looking at their tablets,
they barely even talked to me.

429
00:25:59,829 --> 00:26:01,765
Aren't your parents worried about you?

430
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:07,771
My father
has no interest in me whatsoever.

431
00:26:07,837 --> 00:26:11,641
That's not true. What about your mother…

432
00:26:11,708 --> 00:26:12,575
I don't have one.

433
00:26:12,642 --> 00:26:13,677
What?

434
00:26:13,743 --> 00:26:15,578
My mother died five years ago.

435
00:26:16,746 --> 00:26:17,914
An accident? Illness?

436
00:26:17,981 --> 00:26:19,649
That's enough already!

437
00:26:19,716 --> 00:26:21,418
I'm not going to school anymore.

438
00:26:22,619 --> 00:26:23,920
Don't say that.

439
00:26:23,987 --> 00:26:27,190
Come on, please come.
And give me feedback, Kenta!

440
00:26:28,625 --> 00:26:29,726
Kenta?

441
00:26:37,767 --> 00:26:39,402
Therefore,

442
00:26:40,236 --> 00:26:44,140
tomorrow, why don't we all
go encourage Kenta to come to school?

443
00:26:44,207 --> 00:26:45,108
All of us.

444
00:26:45,709 --> 00:26:46,776
Excuse me.

445
00:26:47,410 --> 00:26:49,079
Why do we have to do that?

446
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:53,783
Tomorrow is a day off,
and aren't you classmates?

447
00:26:53,850 --> 00:26:55,418
If you ask me,

448
00:26:55,485 --> 00:26:58,088
I don't think many people here
think those around them

449
00:26:58,154 --> 00:27:02,125
will become important lifelong friends.

450
00:27:02,726 --> 00:27:03,727
What?

451
00:27:03,793 --> 00:27:06,830
It just so happened
that we ended up in the same class…

452
00:27:06,896 --> 00:27:09,165
Or rather, we're just sharing
the same space.

453
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:14,137
Are you guys saying you don't care
what happens to Kenta?

454
00:27:14,204 --> 00:27:15,805
Don't say it like that…

455
00:27:16,706 --> 00:27:22,045
We were in the same middle school,
but he was also always absent back then.

456
00:27:22,112 --> 00:27:25,148
Don't force your way of thinking on us.

457
00:27:25,215 --> 00:27:29,853
And calling each other by nicknames,
that's just extrovert logic.

458
00:27:30,487 --> 00:27:32,822
It can lead to bullying,

459
00:27:32,889 --> 00:27:36,025
so the school decided
everyone should use honorifics.

460
00:27:36,626 --> 00:27:37,994
Right, Ms. Kashiwabara?

461
00:27:38,561 --> 00:27:39,429
That's right.

462
00:27:41,364 --> 00:27:42,732
Are you serious?

463
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:47,303
Besides, when you state an opinion,
how about you look up

464
00:27:47,370 --> 00:27:49,072
and look the other person in the eye?

465
00:27:53,777 --> 00:27:54,911
-Mr. Onizuka.
-Yes?

466
00:27:54,978 --> 00:27:55,879
That was risky.

467
00:27:55,945 --> 00:27:56,780
What?

468
00:27:56,846 --> 00:27:59,649
If you keep this up,
it will affect your feedback score.

469
00:28:00,784 --> 00:28:01,618
What?

470
00:28:02,218 --> 00:28:03,520
The previous homeroom teacher

471
00:28:03,586 --> 00:28:06,790
also snapped, his score kept
dropping, so he ended up quitting.

472
00:28:06,856 --> 00:28:07,724
Oh, right.

473
00:28:08,258 --> 00:28:09,826
-I see.
-Yes.

474
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:13,196
I wasn't angry, you know.

475
00:28:14,264 --> 00:28:16,900
-Come on, Ms. Kashiwabara. Say something.
-What?

476
00:28:16,966 --> 00:28:18,535
You're the assistant teacher, right?

477
00:28:22,405 --> 00:28:25,041
-Do you know what a perfect number is?
-What?

478
00:28:25,675 --> 00:28:26,810
What is that?

479
00:28:26,876 --> 00:28:30,613
A number where, if you add up all
its divisors, it equals the number itself.

480
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:34,083
To be precise, it's the proper divisors,
excluding the number itself.

481
00:28:34,918 --> 00:28:37,720
I've no idea what you're talking about.

482
00:28:37,787 --> 00:28:43,960
For example,
the divisors of six are one, two…

483
00:28:45,328 --> 00:28:46,729
and three.

484
00:28:46,796 --> 00:28:50,133
When you add them all up, they equal six.

485
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,702
Making six the smallest perfect number.

486
00:28:53,603 --> 00:28:57,373
But what does that have to do
with what we're talking about?

487
00:28:57,440 --> 00:29:01,177
The next smallest
perfect number has divisors of four,

488
00:29:01,911 --> 00:29:04,147
seven, and fourteen.

489
00:29:06,216 --> 00:29:07,917
It's 28.

490
00:29:07,984 --> 00:29:09,419
So?

491
00:29:11,287 --> 00:29:14,824
I was just thinking, the number
of students in this class is 28.

492
00:29:15,725 --> 00:29:16,593
What?

493
00:29:16,659 --> 00:29:20,730
For reference, on a certain
famous watch brand's website,

494
00:29:20,797 --> 00:29:24,167
the date display is apparently
always unified to 28.

495
00:29:24,868 --> 00:29:26,736
Because it looks the most beautiful.

496
00:29:28,304 --> 00:29:29,172
Which means,

497
00:29:29,239 --> 00:29:33,142
Class 1-B has to have 28 people,
isn't that what you mean?

498
00:29:33,209 --> 00:29:34,143
Right.

499
00:29:34,644 --> 00:29:37,046
If Kenta isn't here,
this class isn't complete.

500
00:29:37,780 --> 00:29:40,283
Tomorrow, let's gather
in front of his house

501
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:42,252
and convince him to come to school.

502
00:29:42,318 --> 00:29:44,687
Right? I'm sure Kenta will be happy too.

503
00:29:55,832 --> 00:29:58,534
Not a single person came, huh.

504
00:30:16,519 --> 00:30:19,255
What? Is he not home?

505
00:30:25,828 --> 00:30:26,963
What are you doing, Kenta?

506
00:30:28,364 --> 00:30:29,999
What? Hey!

507
00:30:30,066 --> 00:30:31,067
Kenta!

508
00:30:36,205 --> 00:30:37,373
Are you okay?

509
00:30:38,508 --> 00:30:39,509
What?

510
00:30:43,913 --> 00:30:44,781
What is this?

511
00:30:44,847 --> 00:30:45,882
What are you doing?

512
00:30:50,019 --> 00:30:52,822
That's my line. What is this?

513
00:30:53,323 --> 00:30:57,126
I was experimenting to see
if I would die if I jumped from here.

514
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:58,428
What?

515
00:30:58,494 --> 00:31:00,530
And the landing spot seemed pretty good,

516
00:31:01,164 --> 00:31:04,000
my dad would find me right away
when he gets home.

517
00:31:04,067 --> 00:31:06,069
I've decided on jumping from here.

518
00:31:06,135 --> 00:31:07,870
Stop saying such stupid things.

519
00:31:07,937 --> 00:31:11,174
No matter what happens,
I won't let you die.

520
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:13,409
Then what would you do
if I jumped right now?

521
00:31:15,011 --> 00:31:16,446
I'll catch you.

522
00:31:17,180 --> 00:31:19,949
No matter what happens,
I will protect you.

523
00:31:21,985 --> 00:31:23,586
Then can I test it?

524
00:31:24,153 --> 00:31:24,988
What?

525
00:31:25,054 --> 00:31:27,623
To check if you'll really protect me,

526
00:31:28,558 --> 00:31:30,793
I'm going to drop this doll, so catch it.

527
00:31:31,327 --> 00:31:33,763
Oh, it's the same weight as me,

528
00:31:33,830 --> 00:31:36,099
so I think it's pretty heavy.
Are you sure?

529
00:31:36,165 --> 00:31:37,266
All right.

530
00:31:38,568 --> 00:31:39,902
Then bring that thing over.

531
00:31:46,309 --> 00:31:47,143
Here I go.

532
00:31:47,744 --> 00:31:49,645
All right, come on.

533
00:31:57,387 --> 00:31:58,521
See, you failed.

534
00:31:58,588 --> 00:32:00,189
No, that was unfair!

535
00:32:00,256 --> 00:32:02,425
You have to say,
"Ready, set, go" or something.

536
00:32:02,492 --> 00:32:04,927
I need to get mentally prepared too.

537
00:32:05,628 --> 00:32:07,363
I'll give you one more chance.

538
00:32:07,864 --> 00:32:09,132
With a different method.

539
00:32:09,699 --> 00:32:11,100
Different method?

540
00:32:11,167 --> 00:32:12,135
What?

541
00:32:17,407 --> 00:32:20,777
I'm going to drop it into the river
from here. Will you save it?

542
00:32:22,445 --> 00:32:24,047
Yeah, all right.

543
00:32:24,113 --> 00:32:25,648
Here I go!

544
00:32:57,547 --> 00:33:00,116
This time, I saved this thing!

545
00:33:00,183 --> 00:33:03,453
Be careful, the current is fast here.

546
00:33:08,124 --> 00:33:09,926
Hey, help me.

547
00:33:12,261 --> 00:33:15,031
Wait, hey…

548
00:33:15,565 --> 00:33:18,734
Hey, hold on…

549
00:33:20,236 --> 00:33:21,437
You failed.

550
00:33:21,504 --> 00:33:23,139
In the end, the doll washed away.

551
00:33:24,307 --> 00:33:28,077
You can't blame me, it absorbs water,
so it got incredibly heavy.

552
00:33:28,678 --> 00:33:30,279
Why don't you just give up?

553
00:33:30,346 --> 00:33:32,882
There's no point
in protecting someone like me.

554
00:33:32,949 --> 00:33:34,417
No way that is true.

555
00:33:34,484 --> 00:33:37,720
Please, one more chance. One more chance.

556
00:33:37,787 --> 00:33:40,456
Fine. Then take out your phone.

557
00:33:40,523 --> 00:33:41,357
What?

558
00:33:42,125 --> 00:33:43,092
Your phone.

559
00:33:45,328 --> 00:33:46,162
Sure.

560
00:33:46,929 --> 00:33:49,265
What? You're still using a flip phone?

561
00:33:49,332 --> 00:33:52,702
Idiot. It's a low-spec smartphone.
It can even do video calls.

562
00:33:52,768 --> 00:33:54,070
Then tell me your number.

563
00:34:03,246 --> 00:34:04,480
Wait here.

564
00:34:04,547 --> 00:34:05,948
I'll call right away.

565
00:34:06,449 --> 00:34:09,352
Hey, wait, what are you planning on doing?

566
00:34:18,261 --> 00:34:20,596
KATAYAMA

567
00:34:20,663 --> 00:34:22,798
My mother died five years ago.

568
00:34:44,620 --> 00:34:45,855
Hello?

569
00:34:45,922 --> 00:34:47,890
Mr. Onizuka, can you see me?

570
00:34:50,126 --> 00:34:52,061
What? Yeah.

571
00:34:54,430 --> 00:34:55,364
What?

572
00:34:55,898 --> 00:34:57,867
What are you doing?

573
00:34:58,434 --> 00:35:01,037
I'm going to hang myself now.
Will you come save me?

574
00:35:01,103 --> 00:35:05,541
The door has a sturdy lock on it,
so getting inside is going to be tough.

575
00:35:06,108 --> 00:35:08,311
Wait, you! You're joking, right?

576
00:35:10,446 --> 00:35:13,082
Well, here I go.

577
00:35:14,050 --> 00:35:15,618
You've got to be kidding!

578
00:35:32,335 --> 00:35:35,338
Kenta! Stop messing around!

579
00:35:35,905 --> 00:35:38,274
Hurry up, I'm going to die!

580
00:35:39,075 --> 00:35:39,976
Kenta!

581
00:35:40,610 --> 00:35:41,444
Kenta!

582
00:35:41,510 --> 00:35:44,413
Mr. Onizuka! Hurry up! It hurts!

583
00:35:45,047 --> 00:35:46,315
I'm going in!

584
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:52,388
Wait for me!

585
00:35:54,724 --> 00:35:55,958
My students…

586
00:35:56,826 --> 00:35:58,127
I won't let…

587
00:35:58,194 --> 00:35:59,762
any of them die!

588
00:36:03,466 --> 00:36:04,800
Kenta!

589
00:36:04,867 --> 00:36:06,068
Are you okay?

590
00:36:13,342 --> 00:36:14,243
Kenta!

591
00:36:16,312 --> 00:36:17,213
Hey!

592
00:36:26,856 --> 00:36:28,424
-Anything but that.
-What?

593
00:36:30,126 --> 00:36:31,394
I'm okay!

594
00:36:31,460 --> 00:36:33,996
This is a harness
used for shooting films and such.

595
00:36:34,063 --> 00:36:35,631
This is a rehearsal too.

596
00:36:35,698 --> 00:36:37,767
You can't prank people like this!

597
00:36:38,968 --> 00:36:41,404
What's going on?

598
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:46,275
What are you doing, Kenta?

599
00:36:53,549 --> 00:36:54,884
I am terribly sorry!

600
00:36:55,618 --> 00:36:58,754
We were fooling around a bit,
but I broke your door.

601
00:36:58,821 --> 00:37:01,090
I'll pay you back for it!

602
00:37:01,757 --> 00:37:04,460
That won't be necessary.
Please leave us alone.

603
00:37:04,527 --> 00:37:06,228
Wait, please!

604
00:37:06,295 --> 00:37:07,830
I have one request.

605
00:37:09,198 --> 00:37:10,199
What is it?

606
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:16,038
Could you, as his father,
help convince him to come to school?

607
00:37:16,605 --> 00:37:17,440
Okay?

608
00:37:18,274 --> 00:37:21,243
He can do whatever he wants.

609
00:37:21,811 --> 00:37:22,578
What?

610
00:37:22,645 --> 00:37:25,948
It doesn't seem like
he has anything he wants to do.

611
00:37:26,015 --> 00:37:29,685
And even if his grades are bad,
the school will let him graduate anyway.

612
00:37:30,286 --> 00:37:31,854
Huh? What?

613
00:37:33,356 --> 00:37:34,423
What do you mean?

614
00:37:36,025 --> 00:37:39,895
My father is an executive of the company
that runs the school.

615
00:37:40,629 --> 00:37:42,365
What? No way!

616
00:37:45,735 --> 00:37:47,303
I'm sorry,

617
00:37:47,870 --> 00:37:50,439
but please stop involving
yourself with my son.

618
00:37:57,279 --> 00:38:00,383
Goodbye, sir.

619
00:38:06,622 --> 00:38:07,823
Kenta,

620
00:38:08,491 --> 00:38:11,093
are you really okay with this?

621
00:38:16,465 --> 00:38:17,466
My mom…

622
00:38:19,034 --> 00:38:20,703
died of COVID.

623
00:38:23,839 --> 00:38:25,074
I see.

624
00:38:26,375 --> 00:38:28,110
Because I passed it to her.

625
00:38:29,979 --> 00:38:30,913
What?

626
00:38:31,814 --> 00:38:35,384
That's why I couldn't see her body,

627
00:38:36,385 --> 00:38:38,387
or even say farewell.

628
00:38:47,897 --> 00:38:49,298
<i>During the funeral,</i>

629
00:38:50,199 --> 00:38:53,636
<i>I saw my father crying</i>
<i>and tried to hold his hand, but…</i>

630
00:39:00,209 --> 00:39:03,946
<i>It was like he was saying,</i>
<i>"This is all your fault."</i>

631
00:39:06,282 --> 00:39:08,517
"You should have been the one to die."

632
00:39:09,285 --> 00:39:10,319
That's how it felt.

633
00:39:10,386 --> 00:39:12,054
No, there's no way…

634
00:39:12,121 --> 00:39:15,825
Since then, I haven't touched my father,
not even once.

635
00:39:17,226 --> 00:39:18,127
What?

636
00:39:18,194 --> 00:39:19,295
Actually,

637
00:39:19,361 --> 00:39:22,364
I haven't touched anyone
since the fifth grade.

638
00:39:27,903 --> 00:39:28,971
I will…

639
00:39:30,439 --> 00:39:31,474
hug you tight.

640
00:39:32,508 --> 00:39:33,375
What?

641
00:39:35,878 --> 00:39:36,812
Come on.

642
00:39:37,580 --> 00:39:39,548
Don't be shy! Come at me!

643
00:39:41,984 --> 00:39:42,818
Come on!

644
00:39:43,752 --> 00:39:45,888
-Here!
-Cut it out!

645
00:39:45,955 --> 00:39:48,824
What is wrong with you?
Just leave me alone already!

646
00:40:01,303 --> 00:40:02,738
Thanks for the meal.

647
00:40:34,103 --> 00:40:35,604
What are you doing?

648
00:40:39,375 --> 00:40:40,309
Nothing.

649
00:40:41,477 --> 00:40:43,612
But the housekeeper said earlier…

650
00:40:44,446 --> 00:40:48,951
"I can tell by the closet,
your mother was a wonderful person."

651
00:40:51,387 --> 00:40:52,621
I see.

652
00:40:56,525 --> 00:41:00,396
I'll contact the housekeeping agency
to ask for a replacement.

653
00:41:02,765 --> 00:41:05,901
Wait a minute! I didn't mean it that way!

654
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:13,943
<i>Yes. Okay.</i>

655
00:41:14,510 --> 00:41:16,178
Just leave a message.

656
00:41:16,245 --> 00:41:18,581
I'm at the staff room,
so I'm hanging up. Bye.

657
00:41:19,715 --> 00:41:21,584
Good morning.

658
00:41:21,650 --> 00:41:23,419
Good morning.

659
00:41:23,485 --> 00:41:25,921
Leisurely as ever, Ms. Kashiwabara.

660
00:41:25,988 --> 00:41:29,191
I'm sorry, my mother called
and she just wouldn't hang up.

661
00:41:29,692 --> 00:41:33,862
Onizuka! What on earth
were you thinking? At your age!

662
00:41:35,764 --> 00:41:37,066
What's going on there?

663
00:41:37,967 --> 00:41:41,870
It seems Mr. Onizuka
caused some trouble at a student's house.

664
00:41:41,937 --> 00:41:44,206
I wonder why they hired
a person like that.

665
00:41:44,273 --> 00:41:46,809
Apparently, he used to be in a biker gang.

666
00:41:46,875 --> 00:41:49,011
Oh, really?

667
00:41:49,645 --> 00:41:51,880
Let's try to stay away from him.

668
00:41:52,481 --> 00:41:55,451
What are biker gangs? Please tell me.

669
00:42:01,290 --> 00:42:04,693
You're already this old!
What were you thinking?

670
00:42:05,561 --> 00:42:09,131
Barging into Mr. Katayama's house,
breaking the door…

671
00:42:09,898 --> 00:42:12,501
That was because Kenta was trying to die.

672
00:42:12,568 --> 00:42:15,204
He was obviously just messing around.

673
00:42:15,270 --> 00:42:17,272
This is a big mess for us.

674
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:22,344
His father filed a complaint, asking why
we hired a violent teacher like you.

675
00:42:22,411 --> 00:42:27,082
Vice Principal, I will explain that matter
to Director Katayama myself.

676
00:42:27,149 --> 00:42:29,852
Miyazawa, you should never have hired him!

677
00:42:29,918 --> 00:42:31,186
I'm sorry.

678
00:42:31,253 --> 00:42:35,324
But I'm sure Mr. Onizuka
was just worried about Kenta.

679
00:42:35,391 --> 00:42:36,392
That's right.

680
00:42:36,458 --> 00:42:39,228
The school needs to take action too,
or it'll be a disaster.

681
00:42:39,294 --> 00:42:43,932
People who make a big fuss
about dying don't go through with it.

682
00:42:43,999 --> 00:42:44,833
Right, Principal?

683
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:46,935
Yeah, besides,

684
00:42:47,002 --> 00:42:51,206
the school can't take responsibility
for a student's family issues…

685
00:42:51,273 --> 00:42:52,675
There are limits, you know.

686
00:42:53,242 --> 00:42:55,678
So you're just going
to leave him like that?

687
00:42:55,744 --> 00:42:58,480
You know that in this era,
not going to school

688
00:42:58,547 --> 00:43:01,950
is also a valid choice, right?

689
00:43:02,017 --> 00:43:05,521
-We teachers can't be saying that!
-Mr. Onizuka, wait a moment!

690
00:43:05,587 --> 00:43:08,257
Ryunosuke, you tell him something too!

691
00:43:09,058 --> 00:43:10,492
I'm sorry.

692
00:43:11,093 --> 00:43:14,196
I'll leave these matters
for the two of you to decide.

693
00:43:14,263 --> 00:43:15,531
What the heck?

694
00:43:17,733 --> 00:43:18,767
Excuse me.

695
00:43:19,268 --> 00:43:20,469
What is it, Ms. Kashiwabara?

696
00:43:20,536 --> 00:43:22,371
I need to tell Mr. Onizuka something.

697
00:43:23,505 --> 00:43:24,540
Okay.

698
00:43:28,277 --> 00:43:29,344
What's the matter?

699
00:43:29,411 --> 00:43:31,013
I found something really bad.

700
00:43:32,014 --> 00:43:33,015
Something bad?

701
00:43:33,082 --> 00:43:35,350
It's Kenta Katayama's social media.

702
00:43:35,417 --> 00:43:37,553
It looks like he's trying to do something…

703
00:43:59,675 --> 00:44:00,642
Kenta.

704
00:44:02,111 --> 00:44:03,345
Yes.

705
00:44:04,413 --> 00:44:05,881
Everyone is already gathered.

706
00:44:15,124 --> 00:44:17,459
Hello, everyone.

707
00:44:17,526 --> 00:44:19,561
It's time, so we'll depart.

708
00:44:20,229 --> 00:44:24,433
We are going to a quiet, remote place,
then we'll fill the car with exhaust gas

709
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:26,735
so we can all die together,
that's the plan.

710
00:44:26,802 --> 00:44:28,103
Let's do this.

711
00:45:09,678 --> 00:45:10,546
It hurts!

712
00:45:10,612 --> 00:45:12,581
What are you doing? It's dangerous!

713
00:45:16,552 --> 00:45:19,755
Kenta,
do you know what a teacher's job is?

714
00:45:20,322 --> 00:45:21,290
What?

715
00:45:22,124 --> 00:45:24,226
It's to protect
the future of their students.

716
00:45:27,296 --> 00:45:29,531
I heard that from someone.

717
00:45:29,598 --> 00:45:31,867
-What's with you?
-Shut up!

718
00:45:32,968 --> 00:45:35,370
My wife went back to her parents' house,

719
00:45:35,437 --> 00:45:37,472
my tooth hurts,
and my dental implants cost money.

720
00:45:37,539 --> 00:45:40,676
I'm in a bad mood!

721
00:45:44,580 --> 00:45:45,447
You idiots.

722
00:45:46,181 --> 00:45:47,516
Every one of you!

723
00:45:47,583 --> 00:45:48,884
Go home already!

724
00:45:56,625 --> 00:45:57,960
You,

725
00:45:58,760 --> 00:46:01,964
how long do you plan
on keeping up with this boring stuff?

726
00:46:05,634 --> 00:46:07,402
Ah, my tooth.

727
00:46:08,370 --> 00:46:12,107
Just now, it hit my lower back too,
so I have to go to the hospital.

728
00:46:12,174 --> 00:46:14,443
Which means more medical bills.

729
00:46:15,444 --> 00:46:16,745
It doesn't matter anyway.

730
00:46:17,279 --> 00:46:20,148
No one in the world cares about me.

731
00:46:20,749 --> 00:46:23,118
Right now, with social division
and global warming,

732
00:46:23,185 --> 00:46:25,387
it doesn't seem like
anything good will happen.

733
00:46:26,955 --> 00:46:28,957
Even so, we have to keep going.

734
00:46:29,691 --> 00:46:31,059
Because we're human.

735
00:46:31,627 --> 00:46:33,929
What, you're quoting Mitsuo Aida?

736
00:46:33,996 --> 00:46:35,264
What?

737
00:46:36,031 --> 00:46:37,266
You actually know Mitsuo?

738
00:46:42,704 --> 00:46:45,173
Because my mother liked him.

739
00:46:47,609 --> 00:46:49,478
Your mother will be sad too,

740
00:46:50,279 --> 00:46:52,147
if you do something stupid.

741
00:46:53,649 --> 00:46:55,717
If you're going to say that, then tell me…

742
00:46:56,251 --> 00:46:57,953
Why shouldn't I die?

743
00:46:59,588 --> 00:47:00,522
What?

744
00:47:01,089 --> 00:47:03,358
Why do I have to stay alive?

745
00:47:04,026 --> 00:47:04,927
Well…

746
00:47:06,862 --> 00:47:08,563
I mean…

747
00:47:10,599 --> 00:47:11,867
So there is no reason.

748
00:47:12,701 --> 00:47:13,802
Nothing matters.

749
00:47:18,573 --> 00:47:20,108
Because…

750
00:47:20,175 --> 00:47:21,643
I would be sad.

751
00:47:26,748 --> 00:47:27,783
What?

752
00:47:31,353 --> 00:47:34,323
If you die, I would be sad.

753
00:47:35,457 --> 00:47:37,659
What's that supposed to mean?

754
00:47:39,494 --> 00:47:41,196
I mean,

755
00:47:41,263 --> 00:47:44,833
we just met and I still don't know
anything about you,

756
00:47:45,667 --> 00:47:48,804
but we managed to do
things together and it was fun.

757
00:47:49,938 --> 00:47:51,273
And besides, look…

758
00:47:52,341 --> 00:47:54,643
I haven't decided
on a nickname for you yet.

759
00:47:55,544 --> 00:47:57,312
"Troublemaker Kid?"

760
00:47:57,379 --> 00:47:58,947
Or "Lonely Boy?"

761
00:48:00,716 --> 00:48:04,052
I want to do lots of fun things with you.

762
00:48:04,753 --> 00:48:06,722
With you and everyone in the class.

763
00:48:07,289 --> 00:48:09,057
My class has 28 people.

764
00:48:09,725 --> 00:48:12,160
Not a single one can be missing.

765
00:48:13,762 --> 00:48:15,063
Are you stupid?

766
00:48:18,767 --> 00:48:20,068
It's enough.

767
00:48:21,136 --> 00:48:23,505
Forgive yourself, Kenta.

768
00:48:25,340 --> 00:48:28,343
It was all COVID's fault.

769
00:48:30,679 --> 00:48:31,880
Not yours.

770
00:48:33,682 --> 00:48:36,485
I'm sure your mother thinks so too.

771
00:48:43,959 --> 00:48:46,028
The only one who can forgive you

772
00:48:47,796 --> 00:48:48,964
is you.

773
00:49:02,577 --> 00:49:03,745
Let's go home.

774
00:49:13,155 --> 00:49:14,289
Get on.

775
00:49:38,447 --> 00:49:40,615
Hold on tight.

776
00:49:43,885 --> 00:49:45,053
Tighter.

777
00:49:45,687 --> 00:49:46,688
Do it right.

778
00:50:00,368 --> 00:50:01,403
Dammit.

779
00:50:03,939 --> 00:50:06,475
Why is it so warm?

780
00:50:09,845 --> 00:50:11,313
Why?

781
00:50:28,630 --> 00:50:29,498
Let's go.

782
00:50:54,589 --> 00:50:56,558
Idiots!

783
00:51:16,611 --> 00:51:18,146
Morning.

784
00:51:21,216 --> 00:51:22,184
What is it?

785
00:51:22,250 --> 00:51:23,084
Nothing.

786
00:51:23,652 --> 00:51:27,088
I was just wondering if you would ask,
"Did something happen?"

787
00:51:27,155 --> 00:51:30,592
I'm sure something happened between you
and Kenta Katayama yesterday.

788
00:51:31,159 --> 00:51:33,962
Well, yes, you could say that.

789
00:51:34,029 --> 00:51:35,530
That happy face of yours…

790
00:51:36,331 --> 00:51:38,567
Does that mean he's coming back?

791
00:51:40,035 --> 00:51:40,936
Yes.

792
00:51:41,002 --> 00:51:41,937
I'm sure.

793
00:51:45,907 --> 00:51:47,809
Good morning.

794
00:51:47,876 --> 00:51:49,945
Good morning, everyone!

795
00:51:53,515 --> 00:51:55,483
What? No way.

796
00:51:59,888 --> 00:52:03,124
Has anyone seen Kenta?

797
00:52:03,959 --> 00:52:05,427
Seems he's absent today too.

798
00:52:06,661 --> 00:52:07,729
That's strange.

799
00:52:08,263 --> 00:52:11,233
Excuse me, could you start homeroom?

800
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:13,568
Ah, sorry.

801
00:52:14,536 --> 00:52:15,370
Right.

802
00:52:16,004 --> 00:52:17,906
I need you all to decide

803
00:52:18,406 --> 00:52:22,911
whether you're going
to major in science or humanities,

804
00:52:22,978 --> 00:52:25,747
so I'll hand the forms out.

805
00:52:34,689 --> 00:52:36,925
Good morning, everyone!

806
00:52:38,126 --> 00:52:42,297
I'm sure you don't remember me,
so I'll introduce myself again.

807
00:52:43,164 --> 00:52:45,767
Kenta Katayama, Cancer, blood type O.

808
00:52:46,301 --> 00:52:47,869
My future dreams…

809
00:52:48,436 --> 00:52:49,337
I have none.

810
00:52:49,904 --> 00:52:51,239
Wait, that's not right,

811
00:52:51,306 --> 00:52:53,775
I plan to find them
during my three years in high school.

812
00:52:53,842 --> 00:52:57,078
Yesterday, I declared that to my father.

813
00:52:57,579 --> 00:52:58,680
I…

814
00:52:59,981 --> 00:53:02,684
I don't plan to work at your company.

815
00:53:04,085 --> 00:53:05,387
But don't worry.

816
00:53:06,121 --> 00:53:08,923
I will never do anything
to cause trouble for you.

817
00:53:09,858 --> 00:53:11,059
So…

818
00:53:14,229 --> 00:53:15,463
won't you shake my hand?

819
00:53:18,500 --> 00:53:22,070
I remembered
what my mother told me a long time ago.

820
00:53:23,305 --> 00:53:25,407
She said that when foreigners shake hands,

821
00:53:26,041 --> 00:53:28,310
it's to declare that they want
to know more

822
00:53:28,376 --> 00:53:29,944
about the other person.

823
00:53:32,314 --> 00:53:33,615
Can't I?

824
00:54:13,588 --> 00:54:15,223
So that's how it is.

825
00:54:15,290 --> 00:54:17,492
I hope we can get along!

826
00:54:26,067 --> 00:54:28,503
Sorry, I forgot something important.

827
00:54:30,305 --> 00:54:31,706
After talking to Onicchi,

828
00:54:31,773 --> 00:54:34,275
I was thinking about
a nickname for myself.

829
00:54:34,342 --> 00:54:36,411
My mom always called me this
when I was little…

830
00:54:37,278 --> 00:54:38,780
Ken-Ken. So call me that!

831
00:55:02,737 --> 00:55:03,638
All right.

832
00:55:04,272 --> 00:55:08,009
Ken-Ken is here too,
our class has become a perfect number.

833
00:55:08,610 --> 00:55:09,444
Everyone.

834
00:55:09,944 --> 00:55:12,180
Let's make today a good day too.

835
00:55:13,014 --> 00:55:15,049
And give me good feedback scores…

836
00:55:15,116 --> 00:55:18,086
Help me get those numbers up! Thank you!

837
00:55:34,269 --> 00:55:36,638
-HE NEVER USES TABLETS AT ALL, WHAT A PAIN
-TOTALLY

838
00:55:36,704 --> 00:55:39,207
LET'S GET RID OF ONIZUKA

839
00:55:41,743 --> 00:55:45,447
MR. ONIZUKA GOT A LOW SCORE

840
00:55:45,513 --> 00:55:52,353
MR. ONIZUKA GOT A LOW SCORE

841
00:55:53,588 --> 00:55:56,624
If anything,
you can even call me Great Teacher.

842
00:56:07,302 --> 00:56:10,538
<i>It's like this class has</i>
<i>a hidden mastermind, like on TV…</i>

843
00:56:10,605 --> 00:56:12,507
The reason he confessed his love

844
00:56:12,574 --> 00:56:14,909
was because he wanted
to make the person he loves happy!

845
00:56:14,976 --> 00:56:15,944
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.

